Package com.xtructure.xevolution.operator

Classes that define reproduction operations

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
CrossoverOperator<D> The CrossoverOperator interface describes the methods used in reproduction via crossover, or simply, with a pair of parents.
MutateOperator<D> The MutateOperator describes the methods used in reproduction via mutation, or generally, with a single parent.
Operator<D> The Operator interface describes the basic functionality of reproductive operations used in evolution.
OperatorSelecter<O extends Operator<?>> The OperatorSelecter describes the methods for a collection of Operators that are retrieved probabilistically, without replacement.
